00:14:52.520 --> 00:14:56.050
by Jane Eyre called
"Reader I married him."

00:14:56.050 --> 00:15:01.930
And it's all female writers;
British and American Canadian.

00:15:01.930 --> 00:15:10.940
There's a woman from Istanbul, and
I wrote a story about a wedding.

00:15:10.940 --> 00:15:13.580
I'll just read the beginning of it.

00:15:13.580 --> 00:15:15.880
It's called "Double Men."

00:15:16.930 --> 00:15:19.960
A friendship that fails
to negotiate dogs

00:15:19.960 --> 00:15:22.340
and chickens is doomed to wither.

00:15:22.340 --> 00:15:26.700 position:56%
Even a friendship that has weathered
decades of hardship and tedium.

00:15:26.700 --> 00:15:29.990
Mama Lota and Nangela had
raised their children together,

00:15:29.990 --> 00:15:32.730
performed birth and
death rites in tandem,

00:15:32.730 --> 00:15:36.040
carried loads light
and heavy as one.

00:15:36.040 --> 00:15:38.130
Now that there were no men
left in their households,

00:15:38.130 --> 00:15:40.950
they depended on each other,
hooked to their everday's,

00:15:40.950 --> 00:15:43.980
the tasks attending
to body and home,

00:15:43.980 --> 00:15:48.600
and a small field they grew enough
greens, beans, potatoes, cassava,

00:15:48.600 --> 00:15:52.510 position:56%
yams, ground nuts, and maize to feed
themselves; and kept the surplus

00:15:52.510 --> 00:15:54.540
in Mama Lota's storehouse.

00:15:54.540 --> 00:15:56.580
