00:45:29.340 --> 00:45:30.820
across on what's called a drift.

00:45:30.820 --> 00:45:34.520
So it's a calm place in the water
that you can drift things across,

00:45:34.520 --> 00:45:37.280
and they made a settlement
called the Old Drift.

00:45:37.280 --> 00:45:40.500
They also come to what
they call black fever

00:45:40.500 --> 00:45:42.210
which is actually malaria.

00:45:42.210 --> 00:45:47.340
So there's a little graveyard there
called the Old Drift Cemetery.

00:45:47.340 --> 00:45:51.620
And so, I'm interested in
those kinds of migrations

00:45:51.620 --> 00:45:54.090
or immigrations into Zambia.

00:45:54.090 --> 00:45:55.910
So I have people coming from India.

00:45:55.910 --> 00:45:59.710
People coming from England
and people coming from Italy.

00:45:59.710 --> 00:46:05.080
And as a way of understanding
the international kind of context

00:46:05.080 --> 00:46:09.700
in which I grew up
in the 70s, late 80s.

00:46:09.700 --> 00:46:14.600
So I'm interested in immigration
to Africa which is kind of reversal

00:46:15.910 --> 00:46:18.110
of the normal way of
thinking about it.

00:46:18.110 --> 00:46:20.090
But in terms of immigration
to America,

00:46:20.090 --> 00:46:22.950
that's still unchartered
territory for me.

00:46:29.910 --> 00:46:33.310
&gt;&gt; Laverne Paige: Those of us who
