summer and I liked it a lot.

00:51:01.560 --> 00:51:02.940
I really love that city.

00:51:02.940 --> 00:51:09.190
I think the racial politics
at Berkley are quite different

00:51:09.190 --> 00:51:12.600
because of the overturning
of a proposition, I think,

00:51:12.600 --> 00:51:14.790
a few years before I got there.

00:51:14.790 --> 00:51:19.190
We can no longer use race as a
determining factor in who we admit

00:51:19.190 --> 00:51:25.940 position:56%
and our population of black students
has accordingly dropped a lot.

00:51:25.940 --> 00:51:27.970
So it's something like 2%.

00:51:27.970 --> 00:51:33.460 position:56%
So it's a very different campus from
what I experienced even at Yale.

00:51:33.460 --> 00:51:38.180
So the diversity on campus
is much more comprised

00:51:38.180 --> 00:51:39.590
of Asian American students

00:51:39.590 --> 00:51:43.310
and Latino/Latina Chicano/Chicana
students.

00:51:43.310 --> 00:51:46.190
So I've learned a lot
about those cultures

00:51:46.190 --> 00:51:50.610
and in teaching my classes that's
been a very interesting aspect is

00:51:50.610 --> 00:51:54.070
seeing these kind of forms
of cultural solidarity

00:51:54.070 --> 00:51:56.770
across the student population.

